<div class="row g-4">
  <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="mb-3">
      <ol class="breadcrumb"><li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/">Home</a></li><li class="breadcrumb-item active">Editorial Policy</li></ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 p-md-5">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span style="background:var(--gradient);width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:12px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">
          <i class="bi bi-journal-check text-white fs-5"></i>
        </span>
        <div>
          <h1 class="h3 fw-bold mb-0">Editorial Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Last updated: January 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <p class="lead">ApolloNews is committed to editorial excellence, independence, and integrity. This policy describes the principles that guide how we source, select, verify, and publish content.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Editorial Independence</h4>
        <p>ApolloNews maintains strict separation between editorial and commercial functions. Advertising relationships do not influence editorial decisions. No advertiser may request, require, or receive preferential treatment in news coverage or editorial placement.</p>
        <p>No political party, government body, or external organisation exerts control over editorial decisions. Our news selection and editorial direction are determined solely by our editorial team based on public interest and journalistic merit.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Source Standards</h4>
        <p>For aggregated news, we source content exclusively from established and reputable news organisations via licensed APIs. Aggregated sources include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Major national and international wire services (Reuters, AP, AFP)</li>
          <li>Established broadsheet and broadcast news organisations</li>
          <li>Specialist industry publications with editorial standards</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not aggregate content from tabloids with demonstrated histories of fabrication, partisan blogs, press releases presented as news, or unverified social media posts.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Original Content Standards</h4>
        <p>Original articles published on ApolloNews meet the following requirements:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Research-based</strong> — Claims are supported by credible sources, research, or data. Sources are linked or cited where possible.</li>
          <li><strong>Balanced</strong> — On contested topics, we represent multiple credible perspectives rather than advocating for a single viewpoint.</li>
          <li><strong>Transparent</strong> — Opinion and analysis are clearly distinguished from news reporting.</li>
          <li><strong>Attribution</strong> — Quotes, statistics, and information are attributed to their sources.</li>
          <li><strong>Corrections</strong> — Errors are corrected promptly and transparently. See our <a href="/corrections">Corrections Policy</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Conflicts of Interest</h4>
        <p>Editorial contributors are required to disclose any potential conflicts of interest relating to topics they write about. Content with a material conflict of interest will either be reassigned or published with a clear disclosure note.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Sponsored &amp; Native Content</h4>
        <p>Any sponsored, native, or promotional content is clearly labelled as "Sponsored", "Advertisement", or "Promoted" and is visually distinguished from our editorial content. Sponsored content does not influence editorial decisions before or after publication.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Complaints &amp; Feedback</h4>
        <p>We take editorial complaints seriously. If you have a concern about any content published on ApolloNews, please contact us via our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> with specific details of your concern. We will investigate and respond within 5 working days.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

